        p.lead We are honoured to hold Gathering Our Voices 2014 on the traditional territory of the Musqueam, Squamish, and Tsleil-waututh Nations.

        p From March 18th through 21st GOV will hold the floors of the Hyatt Regency and Fairmont hotels in Vancouver, B.C. Young people from all across Canada are invited to join us in a celebration of our culture, values, arts, beliefs, and most importantly, our passion.

        p Up to 2000 youth, chaperones, presenters, exhibitors, elders, volunteers, and other guests will have the opporunity to make new connections, reforge old bonds, rekindle their passions, and discover a new drive. How can we improve the present? How can we create a brighter future for ourselves? Are we prepared to face the upcoming challenges? 

        p Join us and learn from pillars of our community, hear their stories, their stuggles, their triumphs. Then, forge your own way by creating your own special blend of workshops, it's your choice what you learn, just as it's your future. Spend your evenings participating in our live talent show and dance. Finally, reconnect if your roots during our closing cultural morning.
    
